name: Game Characters
description:
Welcome to my new model page dedicated to the characters from various video games.

Each version will represent a different character from the game, rather than an improvement to the model itself.

I have some ideas regarding future creations, but if you have your propositions - feel free to leave them in the comments and I might make that character! :-)

The base model is a mix of various models that were available in late November (Hassan 1.4 for sure, do not remember others) so the base quality is above pure 1.5.

Currently available:

  • Street Fighter - Chun-Li

  • Witcher 3 - Cirilla Fiona Elen Riannon

  • Cyberpunk 2077 - Female V

modelVersions.name: Witcher 3 - Cirilla Fiona Elen Riannon
modelVersions.description: I am aware that the previous Ciri model exists on Civitai (https://civitai.com/models/12/ciri-from-the-witcher) but I've tested that one and compared it to mine. That old model is overtrained and it is very hard to do something else than what it was trained for, while mine is not only more flexible but also seems to have better quality outputs.

modelVersions.name: Cyberpunk 2077 - Female V
modelVersions.description:
This model is quite personal since it is my character of V from Cyberpunk 2077.

This model was done as a case study to see if this idea is viable and it proved to be a total success. I spent with that character around 150 hours and now she comes to life!

NOTE: This is also a nice technique to create consistent characters if you wish to make some comics/graphics/illustrations - just create a character in the game (or some META character) and dreambooth it! As you can see in the examples - it can turn out quite marvelous.

modelVersions.name: Street Fighter - Chun-Li
modelVersions.description:
This model was trained on the same day as the TI version from @LucyFanboy ( https://civitai.com/models/5542 ) so I wasn't even sure if I should post it but after the discussion, the decision was made.

You can use this model on its own, you can even combine it with the TI for more interesting results!

And you can even merge it with other models (there is an example from samdoesart merge).

You can do anime, cartoons, renders, photorealistic, paintings, etc - whatever you wish :)

As per usual, the training data is included so if you feel like this does not need to be a checkpoint, you can train Lora, IT, or whatever you feel like :)

Since the limit was 20, here are the rest test images that I've made: https://imgur.com/a/JyntIA2
